body:
>I had no issue with v0.3.3. However I had problem with 0.4.0, that I cannot reproduce now, 

Oh, sorry.

@Hugal31 we're not using alpha6, we're using a git commit after alpha6, without the bug you're talking about, so everything should work. It's strange since alpha6 didn't introduce anything to X11 which can relate to your problem. The only thing that could explain is that your WM is forwarding something to alacritty.(Like I see in your print events).

Reading https://docs.rs/winit/0.20.0/winit/event/enum.WindowEvent.html it looks like `is_synthetic` might be relevant:

```
is_synthetic: bool

If true, the event was generated synthetically by winit in one of the following circumstances:
    Synthetic key press events are generated for all keys pressed when a window gains focus. Likewise, synthetic key release events are generated for all keys pressed when a window goes out of focus. Currently, this is only functional on X11 and Windows

Otherwise, this value is always false.
```

In my case when I switch to workspace with active `alacritty` I still hold `Ctrl-F6` buttons and that event gets delivered as synthetic. I seem to get only a key when I switch to `alacritty` (`Ctrl-F6`), but no when I switch away from it (`Ctrl-F7`). Even though both events seem to be delivered:

```
$ cat first-bad-1cfb0740bc530da3162292bbf682a234240f26a3.txt  | egrep 'F[67]'

[2020-01-12 23:58] [INFO] glutin event: DeviceEvent { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(9))), event: Key(KeyboardInput { scancode: 65, state: Pressed, virtual_keycode: Some(F7), modifiers: CTRL }) }
[2020-01-12 23:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(134217730))), event: KeyboardInput { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(3))), input: KeyboardInput { scancode: 65, state: Released, virtual_keycode: Some(F7), modifiers: CTRL }, is_synthetic: true } }
[2020-01-12 23:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(134217730))), event: KeyboardInput { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(3))), input: KeyboardInput { scancode: 65, state: Released, virtual_keycode: Some(F7), modifiers: CTRL }, is_synthetic: true } }
[2020-01-12 23:58] [INFO] glutin event: DeviceEvent { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(9))), event: Key(KeyboardInput { scancode: 65, state: Released, virtual_keycode: Some(F7), modifiers: CTRL }) }

[2020-01-12 23:58] [INFO] glutin event: DeviceEvent { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(9))), event: Key(KeyboardInput { scancode: 64, state: Pressed, virtual_keycode: Some(F6), modifiers: CTRL }) }
[2020-01-12 23:58] [INFO] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(X(WindowId(134217730))), event: KeyboardInput { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(3))), input: KeyboardInput { scancode: 64, state: Pressed, virtual_keycode: Some(F6), modifiers: CTRL }, is_synthetic: true } }
[2020-01-12 23:58] [INFO] glutin event: DeviceEvent { device_id: DeviceId(X(DeviceId(9))), event: Key(KeyboardInput { scancode: 64, state: Released, virtual_keycode: Some(F6), modifiers: CTRL }) }
```

Cloud it be that `alacritty` gets confused by currently pressed buttons when currently pressed buttons change between synthetic-only events?
